        <section id="spaghetti">
            <h2>Spaghetti Recipe</h2>
            <p>Here is a simple recipe for spaghetti:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Boil water in a large pot.</li>
                <li>Add salt and spaghetti to the boiling water.</li>
                <li>Cook spaghetti until al dente.</li>
                <li>Drain spaghetti and toss with your favorite sauce.</li>
                <li>Serve hot.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="fettuccine-alfredo">
            <h2>Fettuccine Alfredo Recipe</h2>
            <p>Here is a delicious recipe for fettuccine alfredo:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Cook fettuccine according to package instructions.</li>
                <li>In a saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.</li>
                <li>Add minced garlic and cook until fragrant.</li>
                <li>Stir in heavy cream and grated Parmesan cheese.</li>
                <li>Season with salt and pepper to taste.</li>
                <li>Combine cooked fettuccine with the sauce.</li>
                <li>Serve hot, garnished with chopped parsley.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="lasagna">
            <h2>Lasagna Recipe</h2>
            <p>Here is a classic recipe for lasagna:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).</li>
                <li>Cook lasagna noodles according to package instructions.</li>
                <li>In a skillet, cook ground beef with onions and garlic until browned.</li>
                <li>Stir in tomato sauce and Italian seasoning.</li>
                <li>In a baking dish, layer lasagna noodles, meat sauce, and ricotta cheese.</li>
                <li>Repeat layers and top with mozzarella cheese.</li>
                <li>Bake for 30-35 minutes until bubbly and golden.</li>
                <li>Let it cool for a few minutes before serving.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </main>

